import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['delay'])]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='red', label='Median delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['distance'], ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='counts', y='origin', data=data, hue='destination', dodge=False)
    chart.axvline(x=data['counts'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['counts'].max()))
    chart.set(xlabel='Number of Flights', ylabel='Airport Code')
    chart.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby('date').count().reset_index()
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of flights over time?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
